author: stsp
msg: Follow-up to r1388673, fix failing mergeinfo tests.
(no_mergeinfo): Expect an ASCII mergeinfo diagram as output which shows
that no merges have been made yet. I've only done this for this single
test since it's not clear if we want to test the graph drawing in every
mergeinfo test. And maybe there is a better way of testing the graph, e.g.
by generating the expected graph on the fly rather than defining it
non_inheritable_mergeinfo): Make these pass by adding a --show-revs=merged
(run_and_verify_mergeinfo): Allow expected output to be one huge string
so that ASCII diagram output can be special-cased.
